# Roles & Permissions

## Portal roles (`user_profile.portal_role`)

| Role | Access |
|------|--------|
| `admin` | Full access + Users & roles management |
| `guest` | Sign in only; redirected to `/pending` |
| `member` | Access via department role matrix |

## Department roles (`access_role` + `user_department_role`)

Roles are **CRUD-managed** by admins at `/users` (Manager, HR, Viewer seeded by default).

Each role defines permission flags: employee read/write/delete, department read/write, facility read/write.

**Org scope:** `employeeWrite`, `departmentWrite`, and `facilityWrite` apply only to the user’s assigned department/facility rows. Creating new departments or facilities is **admin-only**. `departmentReadAll` / `facilityReadAll` grant global read, not global write.

Users get per-department assignments via `roleId` FK.

## Bootstrap

- First user (email or GitHub) → `admin`
- Later self-signups → `guest`
- Invited users → pre-assigned `admin` or `member` + department roles (not guest)

## Guards

- `requireUser` — authenticated
- `requireAppAccess` — not guest; has admin or ≥1 department role
- `requireAdmin` — portal admin only
- `requireDashboardAccess` — `navDashboard` (or admin)
- `requireEmployeesAccess` — `navEmployees` + employee capability
- `requireDepartmentsAccess` — `navDepartments` + department capability
- `requireFacilitiesAccess` — `navFacilities` + facility capability
- `requirePharmacyAccess` — `navPharmacy` + pharmacy capability
- `requireToolsAccess` — `navTools` (or admin)
- `requireSettingsAccess` — `navSettings` (or admin)
- `requireCommunityManage` — `navCommunity` (or admin). **Not** `navDashboard`.

Each private sidebar page has a matching layout/API guard. Nav flags only control visibility/access; content CRUD still uses the capability flags (employeeWrite, etc.).

Services accept `UserPermissions` from `getUserPermissions(userId)`.

## Invites

- Admin UI: `/users` → invite form → email with `/auth/accept-invite?token=…`
- Single-use token, 24h expiry, resend/revoke from admin UI
- Accept: password only (name/roles pre-chosen)

